title: 2019–20 Austrian Football Second League
text:
The 2019–20 <a href="Austrian%20Football%20Second%20League">Austrian Football Second League</a> is the 46th season of the <a href="Austria">Austria</a>n second-level <a href="Association%20football">football</a> league and the second one as the Second League. The league contains 16 teams with one team being promoted to the <a href="Austrian%20Football%20Bundesliga">Austrian Football Bundesliga</a> and 3 teams being relegated to the <a href="Austrian%20Regionalliga">Austrian Regionalliga</a>.
Teams.
Sixteen teams will participate in the 2019–20 season. Promoted teams are <a href="Grazer%20AK">Grazer AK</a> from <a href="2018%E2%80%9319%20Austrian%20Regionalliga">Austrian Regionalliga Central</a> and <a href="FC%20Dornbirn%201913">FC Dornbirn 1913</a> from <a href="2018%E2%80%9319%20Austrian%20Regionalliga">Austrian Regionalliga West</a>. No team gained promotion from <a href="2018%E2%80%9319%20Austrian%20Regionalliga">Austrian Regionalliga East</a> due to the only team to apply for a licence (<a href="SK%20Rapid%20Wien">SK Rapid Wien II</a>) not attaining the required second place.
The team relegated from the <a href="2018%E2%80%9319%20Austrian%20Football%20Bundesliga">2018–19 Austrian Football Bundesliga</a> were <a href="FC%20Wacker%20Innsbruck%20%282002%29">Wacker Innsbruck</a>.
